-- Oliver Suess
-- 2010-07-07T05:05:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/germans-reveal-previously-undeclared-bank-accounts-handelsblatt-reports.html

          
          
             A total of 21,734 Germans have
reported since February hitherto undeclared bank accounts in
Switzerland, Luxemburg and Liechtenstein,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing a survey of finance authorities in Germanyâ€™s 16 states.  
 Germany stands to gain at least 1.5 billion euros ($1.9
billion) in tax revenue from the voluntary disclosures, which
enable tax dodgers to avoid punishment.  
